      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "Hey Lee — thanks for bringing this up, and I'm really glad you did. Two weeks of sharp knee pain is absolutely worth taking seriously, and it makes sense that you're trying to figure out the right call here.\n\nI want to be straightforward with you: **diagnosing what's causing your knee pain is genuinely outside my lane as a coach.** Sharp pain that's persisted for two weeks, especially with that stair-specific pattern, is something a sports medicine physician or physiotherapist needs to assess in person. They can actually see what's happening and rule out things I simply can't evaluate from here.\n\nOn the ibuprofen question — same boundary applies. Whether or how to use any medication before or during runs is a medical question, and I'd really encourage you to ask the doctor or physio that directly when you see them.\n\n---\n\n**What I *can* tell you from a coaching standpoint:**\n\nContinuing to run through sharp, persistent pain — even at reduced distances — carries real risk. Pain that sharp is often your body signaling that something needs attention, not just modification. Shortening runs might reduce load, but it doesn't address whatever is driving the pain, and in some cases it can delay healing or make things worse.\n\nThe most protective thing you can do for your **July 11th goal right now is to get this properly evaluated.** You have about 16 weeks to race day — that's actually enough runway to recover, rebuild, and still run a strong half marathon, *if* you get clarity soon rather than letting this linger.\n\n---\n\n**Your history with IT band tightness is also worth mentioning to the clinician** — not because I'm assuming that's what this is, but because it's useful context for them.\n\nOnce you have medical clearance and a clearer picture of what's going on, I'm ready to work with whatever timeline and constraints you're given. We'll figure out the right path forward together.\n\n**Can I ask — do you have access to a sports medicine doc or physio you could reach out to this week?**"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01EuZcH7oz1sJtMveNdJ9qK6"
    }
